BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 589.30 Tm (could create, read, update, and delete students. It worked. But, between you and me, it was a bit) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 574.10 Tm (rough around the edges. Today, we take that rough, working code and make it professional - the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 558.90 Tm (kind of code you would be proud to ship at a real company.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 538.70 Tm (We will do three things. First, we will organise our code into clean layers, so each part has one) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 523.50 Tm (clear job. Second, we will stop exposing our raw database objects to the outside world - we will) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 508.30 Tm (use something called a DTO. And third, we will handle errors gracefully, so that when something) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 493.10 Tm (goes wrong, the caller gets a clear, friendly message instead of an ugly crash.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 472.90 Tm (And then, to finish, we will take a first peek at two big topics - Spring Security and microservices -) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 457.70 Tm (just to see the road ahead. So today is really about turning a beginner's app into a grown-up one.) Tj ET
