BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 656.50 Tm (Quick warm-up, three questions - answer in your head, then we reveal.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 636.30 Tm (Question one: what does at-RequestBody do? Think... Reveal. It takes the JSON sent in the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 621.10 Tm (request body and turns it into a Java object for you, automatically. You put it on a method) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 605.90 Tm (parameter, and Spring hands you a ready-filled object.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 585.70 Tm (Question two: what is the difference between POST and PUT? Think... Reveal. POST creates a) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 570.50 Tm (brand-new thing - that is the C in CRUD. PUT updates something that already exists, usually) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 555.30 Tm (found by an id in the address - that is the U.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 535.10 Tm (And question three: what does at-PathVariable do? Reveal. It pulls a value straight out of the URL) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 519.90 Tm (path. In slash posts slash five, the 'five' gets handed to your method as the id.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 499.70 Tm (All comfortable? Lovely. Notice today we are switching from students to posts - blog posts - as our) Tj ET
