BT /F1 10.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 335.80 Tm (exposing only safe fields.) Tj ET
0.720 0.720 0.760 rg 58.00 322.30 3.00 49.00 re f
BT /F2 9.50 Tf 0.040 0.340 0.780 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 311.30 Tm (SAY \(read this aloud\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 295.30 Tm (Let's start with a problem you might not even realise you have. In Session 2, our controller) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 280.10 Tm (returned the very same object that maps to the database. It was convenient - but it is actually) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 264.90 Tm (dangerous. Let me show you why.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 244.70 Tm (Look at the left panel. We return a User object straight from the database. But think about what is) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 229.50 Tm (on a real User record - the name and email, sure, but also the password, an 'is-admin' flag, maybe) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 214.30 Tm (a count of failed login attempts. And when you return that whole object, ALL of it gets sent out to) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 199.10 Tm (the caller - including the password. You have just leaked sensitive data to the outside world) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 183.90 Tm (without meaning to. Yikes.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 163.70 Tm (Now the right panel. Here we return a UserDTO - a separate object that contains only the safe) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 148.50 Tm (fields: name, email, role. The password and the internal flags simply are not in it, so they cannot) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 133.30 Tm (leak.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 113.10 Tm (Here is the core problem in one sentence. Your database table and your public response are two) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 97.90 Tm (different things, with two different audiences. When you let one be the other, you tie them together) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 82.70 Tm (- and you accidentally expose things you never intended. The fix is a dedicated object just for) Tj ET
