BT /F1 10.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 238.90 Tm (A vertical pipeline: Client, Controller, Service, Repository, Database, each labelled with its annotation and) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 225.40 Tm (responsibility.) Tj ET
0.720 0.720 0.760 rg 58.00 211.90 3.00 49.00 re f
BT /F2 9.50 Tf 0.040 0.340 0.780 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 200.90 Tm (SAY \(read this aloud\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 184.90 Tm (This slide is the backbone of the whole session, so let's go slowly. A professional Spring Boot app) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 169.70 Tm (is split into layers, and each layer has exactly one job. A request flows down through them, and) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 154.50 Tm (the response flows back up. Let me walk you down the pipeline.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 134.30 Tm (The Client - a browser, a phone, a testing tool - sends an HTTP request. It arrives at the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 119.10 Tm (Controller, marked at-RestController. The controller's only job is to deal with the web - take the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 103.90 Tm (request, and pass a DTO down to the service. Then the Service, marked at-Service, holds the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 88.70 Tm (business logic - the actual thinking - and it does the mapping between DTO and entity. The service) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 73.50 Tm (calls the Repository, marked at-Repository, whose only job is talking to the database using the) Tj ET
