BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 520.60 Tm (Let me introduce a wonderful little time-saver called Lombok. Here is the problem it solves. In) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 505.40 Tm (Java, for every class with fields, you end up writing the same boring code over and over - getters,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 490.20 Tm (setters, a toString, equals, hashCode. Pages of it. It is repetitive and nobody enjoys it.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 470.00 Tm (Lombok generates all of that for you, automatically, when the code compiles. You just add one) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 454.80 Tm (annotation. Look at the table. at-Data is the all-in-one - it gives you getters, setters, toString,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 439.60 Tm (equals, and hashCode, all at once. at-AllArgsConstructor makes a constructor with every field.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 424.40 Tm (at-NoArgsConstructor makes an empty one. And at-Builder gives a nice builder style.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 404.20 Tm (Look at the before-and-after on screen. Thirty lines of boring code on the left, shrinks to about five) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 389.00 Tm (lines on the right, with just at-Data on top. Same result, a fraction of the typing. It is like a tool that) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 373.80 Tm (fills in all the standard paperwork for you and just leaves you the parts that actually matter.) Tj ET
