BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 128.70 Tm (Let me introduce a helpful Java idea called Optional, because it is how we throw that exception) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 113.50 Tm (cleanly. When you ask the database 'find me post number five' using findById, it does not just) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 98.30 Tm (hand you a post or crash. Instead it hands you an Optional - which is like a little box that might) Tj ET
