BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 754.00 Tm (- you must handle both'.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 733.80 Tm (And handling both is easy with one method - orElseThrow. Follow the two paths on screen.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 718.60 Tm (findById gives you the box. If the post is inside, orElseThrow opens the box and hands it to you. If) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 703.40 Tm (the box is empty, orElseThrow throws your ResourceNotFoundException - which becomes the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 688.20 Tm (clean 404. Read the code out loud and it almost makes sense in plain English: 'find by id, or else) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 673.00 Tm (throw this exception'.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 652.80 Tm (So with one line, you handle the happy case and the missing case, no messy null checks needed.) Tj ET
