0.720 0.720 0.760 rg 58.00 683.50 3.00 35.50 re f
BT /F2 9.50 Tf 0.040 0.340 0.780 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 672.50 Tm (SAY \(read this aloud\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 656.50 Tm (To understand microservices, we first need to understand what they replace - the monolith. So far,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 641.30 Tm (everything we have built is a monolith. That just means one single application, one deployable) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 626.10 Tm (unit, with all the features bundled together inside it. And honestly, for starting out, that is perfectly) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 610.90 Tm (fine. But as a system grows huge, the monolith starts to hurt. Let me show you the three pains.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 590.70 Tm (Pain one - one failure can take everything down. If the payments part crashes badly, it can drag) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 575.50 Tm (the whole application down with it, including the parts that were working fine. No isolation. Pain) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 560.30 Tm (two - you cannot scale just one part. Say only the orders feature is getting hammered with traffic.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 545.10 Tm (To handle it, you have to duplicate the entire giant app, wasting resources on all the parts that) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 529.90 Tm (were not even busy. And pain three - risky deployments. A tiny one-line change to the inventory) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 514.70 Tm (feature means rebuilding and redeploying the whole massive application. So releases become) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 499.50 Tm (slow and scary.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 479.30 Tm (Picture one enormous ship carrying everything - if one engine fails, the whole ship stops, and you) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 464.10 Tm (cannot make just one part of it faster.) Tj ET
0.040 0.520 1.000 rg 58.00 448.90 3.00 229.60 re f
BT /F2 15.00 Tf 0.100 0.100 0.120 rg 1 0 0 1 58.00 429.90 Tm (Slide 15 - Microservices architecture: the solution) Tj ET
0.040 0.520 1.000 rg 58.00 412.90 496.00 1.40 re f
BT /F2 9.50 Tf 0.420 0.420 0.460 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 396.90 Tm (ON SCREEN) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 380.90 Tm (The same system split into independent services, each with its own database, and three benefit cards.) Tj ET
0.720 0.720 0.760 rg 58.00 367.40 3.00 35.50 re f
BT /F2 9.50 Tf 0.040 0.340 0.780 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 356.40 Tm (SAY \(read this aloud\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 340.40 Tm (So here is the alternative - microservices. The idea is to break that one giant app into many small,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 325.20 Tm (independent services. Each one owns a single business job, has its own database, and they talk) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 310.00 Tm (to each other over the network, usually with REST - the very thing you have been learning.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 289.80 Tm (Now compare directly with the monolith's three pains. Independent deployment - you can update) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 274.60 Tm (the payment service and ship just that one; the others keep running, untouched. Independent) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 259.40 Tm (scaling - if orders is busy, you run more copies of just the order service; pay only for what you) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 244.20 Tm (actually need. And failure isolation - if payments goes down, users and inventory carry right on) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 229.00 Tm (serving. One failure no longer means total collapse.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 208.80 Tm (Instead of one enormous ship, picture a fleet of small boats. If one has engine trouble, the others) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 193.60 Tm (sail on, and you can speed up just the boats that need it.) Tj ET
0.040 0.520 1.000 rg 58.00 178.40 3.00 184.00 re f
